{
  "stem": "7069.5",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And as the Russians came closer, there was a danger, quote, unquote, 'danger' for the Nazis that we would be liberated.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were not supposed to be liberated.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "By the way, also to interject very quickly, Auschwitz was the largest extermination camp of all the camps.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It is estimated that between 1 and 1/2, closer to 2 million probably, people were killed there.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It's estimated, and on my part, the estimations that I read, probably like 3/4 millions were Poles, whom by that-- by that time Hitler had declared also subhumans.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were killed in Auschwitz, about, let's say, 3/4 million of them.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "About 120 to 150,000 gypsies, whom of course Hitler had declared subhumans.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "A little more, I believe, than a million Jews, somewhat more than a million Jews.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And a rough estimate, out of these Jews, there were probably half a million or a little bit more just children.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Children that had committed the big crime of being born Jewish.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So it was the most horrible killing machine that ever was invented by, I am hesitant to say, human beings.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, as the Russians came closer, we were then ordered-- we were not allowed to survive, not allowed to be rescued.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were then ordered out into marching columns.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were involved in what's called to be a death march.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I will come, really, to the details of a death march a little later.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because there was a second one that I was in.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they are ?] identical to each other.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That I'll-- don't describe this in detail here.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
